efoodietakesflight.com/#website","url":"https://thefoodietakesflight.com/","name":"The Foodie Takes Flight","description":"Delicious vegan and plant-based Asian recipes for everyone","potentialAction":[{"@type":"SearchAction","target":{"@type":"EntryPoint","urlTemplate":"https://thefoodietakesflight.com/?s={search_term_string}"},"query-input":{"@type":"PropertyValueSpecification","valueRequired":true,"valueName":"search_term_string"}}],"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"Person","@id":"https://thefoodietakesflight.com/#/schema/person/dc7e83bd5c29318a17a3ef55ff466716","name":"Jeeca","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","inLanguage":"en-US","@id":"https://thefoodietakesflight.com/#/schema/person/image/","url":"https://thefoodietakesflight.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/jeeca-thumbnail.png","contentUrl":"https://thefoodietakesflight.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/jeeca-thumbnail.png","caption":"Jeeca"},"url":"https://thefoodietakesflight.com/author/thefoodietakesflight/"},{"@type":"Recipe","name":"Shredded Tofu Bulgogi Rice Bowl","author":{"@id":"https://thefoodietakesflight.com/#/schema/person/dc7e83bd5c29318a17a3ef55ff466716"},"description":"Shredding tofu and baking or air-frying it to draw out excess creates a unique texture that almost resembles ground meat. This shredded tofu is cooked down in a bulgogi-style sauce that’s spicy, savoury, a little sweet, and oh-so flavourful. It’s a delicious tofu recipe you can prepare to serve over rice.","datePublished":"2023-01-19T06:16:29+00:00","image":["https://thefoodietakesflight.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/Shredded-Tofu-Bulgogi-Bowl-7-of-8-scaled.jpg","https://thefoodietakesflight.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/Shredded-Tofu-Bulgogi-Bowl-7-of-8-500x500.jpg","https://thefoodietakesflight.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/Shredded-Tofu-Bulgogi-Bowl-7-of-8-500x375.jpg","https://thefoodietakesflight.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/Shredded-Tofu-Bulgogi-Bowl-7-of-8-480x270.jpg"],"video":{"name":"Turn shredded tofu into this bulgogi-style rice bowl 🍚","description":"Get the full recipe 👉🏼 https://thefoodietakesflight.com/shredded-tofu-bulgogi/\n\n#tofu #recipe #vegan","uploadDate":"2023-01-24T15:40:00+00:00","duration":"PT50S","thumbnailUrl":"https://i.ytimg.com/vi/Txk2b4BUMmY/hqdefault.jpg","embedUrl":"https://www.youtube.com/embed/Txk2b4BUMmY?feature=oembed","contentUrl":"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Txk2b4BUMmY","@type":"VideoObject"},"recipeYield":["3","3 people"],"prepTime":"PT25M","cookTime":"PT15M","totalTime":"PT40M","recipeIngredient":["17.5 oz extra firm tofu","1/2 cup grated asian pear (or Fuji apple,  (I peeled mine before grating))","1-2 tbsp soy sauce","1.5 tbsp gochujang","2 tbsp sesame oil","1 tbsp sesame seeds","1 tsp dark soy sauce","2 tbsp sugar","1.5 tsp finely grated ginger","3 cloves garlic (minced)","Chopped green onions","Sesame seeds","Steamed rice (, I used short grain or Japanese sushi rice)"],"recipeInstructions":[{"@type":"HowToSection","name":"SHREDDED TOFU","itemListElement":[{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Remove the tofu from the water and drain from any excess water. Using a cheese grater, carefully grate the tofu into shreds.","name":"Remove the tofu from the water and drain from any excess water. Using a cheese grater, carefully grate the tofu into shreds.","url":"https://thefoodietakesflight.com/shredded-tofu-bulgogi/#wprm-recipe-20872-step-0-0"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Meanwhile, preheat your air-fryer or oven to 350F/180C.","name":"Meanwhile, preheat your air-fryer or oven to 350F/180C.","url":"https://thefoodietakesflight.com/shredded-tofu-bulgogi/#wprm-recipe-20872-step-0-1"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"On a lined baking tray or air fryer basket (I used parchment paper), place the shredded tofu and try to spread it out as thin as possible.","name":"On a lined baking tray or air fryer basket (I used parchment paper), place the shredded tofu and try to spread it out as thin as possible.","url":"https://thefoodietakesflight.com/shredded-tofu-bulgogi/#wprm-recipe-20872-step-0-2"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"For air-frying, air-fry for 12-15 minutes or until lightly golden brown - do not overcook since it can easily harden and become too dry.","name":"For air-frying, air-fry for 12-15 minutes or until lightly golden brown - do not overcook since it can easily harden and become too dry.","url":"https://thefoodietakesflight.com/shredded-tofu-bulgogi/#wprm-recipe-20872-step-0-3"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"You can flip the tofu halfway through cooking. It’s also okay not to get even browning and even have the tofu still white, since this can add to the different textures of the overall tofu dish.","name":"You can flip the tofu halfway through cooking. It’s also okay not to get even browning and even have the tofu still white, since this can add to the different textures of the overall tofu dish.","url":"https://thefoodietakesflight.com/shredded-tofu-bulgogi/#wprm-recipe-20872-step-0-4"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"If baking, you may need to bake the tofu for 25-30 minutes.","name":"If baking, you may need to bake the tofu for 25-30 minutes.","url":"https://thefoodietakesflight.com/shredded-tofu-bulgogi/#wprm-recipe-20872-step-0-5"}]},{"@type":"HowToSection","name":"PREPARE THE SAUCE","itemListElement":[{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"While the tofu is cooking, prepare the sauce by mixing everything together. Feel free to adjust to your taste.","name":"While the tofu is cooking, prepare the sauce by mixing everything together. Feel free to adjust to your taste.","url":"https://thefoodietakesflight.com/shredded-tofu-bulgogi/#wprm-recipe-20872-step-1-0"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Want it really saucy? You can double the sauce!","name":"Want it really saucy? You can double the sauce!","url":"https://thefoodietakesflight.com/shredded-tofu-bulgogi/#wprm-recipe-20872-step-1-1"}]},{"@type":"HowToSection","name":"ADD THE TOFU TO THE SAUCE","itemListElement":[{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Once the tofu is lightly golden brown and crisp on the edges, transfer it to the sauce. Mix well to coat.","name":"Once the tofu is lightly golden brown and crisp on the edges, transfer it to the sauce. Mix well to coat.","url":"https://thefoodietakesflight.com/shredded-tofu-bulgogi/#wprm-recipe-20872-step-2-0"}]},{"@type":"HowToSection","name":"COOKING &amp; SERVING","itemListElement":[{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"In a medium wok or pan, add in the shredded tofu and sauce. Cook down over medium heat for 7-8 minutes or until the sauce has reduced and absorbed by the tofu. The sauce will also slightly thicken from the sugars in the sauce.","name":"In a medium wok or pan, add in the shredded tofu and sauce. Cook down over medium heat for 7-8 minutes or until the sauce has reduced and absorbed by the tofu. The sauce will also slightly thicken from the sugars in the sauce.","url":"https://thefoodietakesflight.com/shredded-tofu-bulgogi/#wprm-recipe-20872-step-3-0"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Taste the tofu and feel free to season more, if desired.","name":"Taste the tofu and feel free to season more, if desired.","url":"https://thefoodietakesflight.com/shredded-tofu-bulgogi/#wprm-recipe-20872-step-3-1"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Turn off the heat. Serve this hot with rice and garnish with some chopped green onions & sesame seeds, if desired. Enjoy!","name":"Turn off the heat. Serve this hot with rice and garnish with some chopped green onions & sesame seeds, if desired. Enjoy!","url":"https://thefoodietakesflight.com/shredded-tofu-bulgogi/#wprm-recipe-20872-step-3-2"}]}],"aggregateRating":{"@type":"AggregateRating","ratingValue":"4.9","ratingCount":"69","reviewCount":"11"},"review":[{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"This was yummy! I doubled the sauce. Will be making in repeat.","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Natasha"},"datePublished":"2026-06-24"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"Amazing taste and texture! Would eat this instead of meat any day.","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Lei"},"datePublished":"2026-06-21"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"Easy and delicious!","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Terez"},"datePublished":"2026-06-17"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"This is so good! Like others said, the sauce should probably be doubled, but I actually like it kind of light because I'm in a calorie deficit, so I'll leave the sauce measurements as is for now. I used high protein tofu and cauliflower rice and I'm definitely going to use this recipe as a staple for the next few months during my cut. It tastes amazing! And shredding tofu was a new one for me. Really loved the texture when it came out of the oven. So glad I finally tried this one!","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Lola"},"datePublished":"2026-06-17"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"I’ve never been a tofu fan, but this recipe was fantastic.  I questioned the huge amount of sesame oil so I excluded it.  I’m planning to add this to the weekly rotation for a while.\r\n\r\nI did have better results after drying the tofu after shredding to get even browning","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Jared"},"datePublished":"2026-04-02"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"Absolutely delicious! We made a triple batch and had it for dinner, and then meal prepped with the leftovers. It was fantastic, served with brown rice, some steamed broccoli, and carrots, and kimchi.","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Cassie Kling"},"datePublished":"2026-03-30"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"4"},"reviewBody":"Did you bake the cauliflower along with the tofu or add it in at the sauce stage?","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Niall"},"datePublished":"2026-03-27"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"4"},"reviewBody":"Before or after you baked the tofu? I.e. Did you bake the carrots with the tofu or throw them in with it into the sauce afterwards?","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Niall"},"datePublished":"2026-03-27"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"This is honestly the best shredded tofu recipe I have ever made, leading to my first recipe rating ever. Flavour is so good. Flipping the tofu over halfway makes a world of difference","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Barb"},"datePublished":"2026-03-26"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"This was so flavourful and I really liked the texture. I'll try this shreading technique with other recipes too. My partner thought it was chicken, so it's a great choice for carnivores. I baked the shredded tofu in the oven for around 30 min. and then sautéed in the sauce until it was fully absorbed by the tofu. I also doubled the amount of sauce as suggested by some.\r\nI'll be adding this recipe into my regular rotation.","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Alicia"},"datePublished":"2026-02-01"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"Wooow. Wow! I'm commenting before taking my next bite because the first was so good. Lovely flavors married with the shredded air-fried tofu technique. It's marvelous. I didn't have pear or apple so I used shredded carrot instead. Thanks for sharing.","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Zarana"},"datePublished":"2026-02-01"}],"recipeCategory":["Main Course"],"recipeCuisine":["Asian","East Asian","Korean"],"keywords":"beef bulgogi, bulgogi sauce, easy tofu recipe, tofu recipes","nutrition":{"@type":"NutritionInformation","servingSize":"1 serving (no rice)","calories":"249 kcal","carbohydrateContent":"19 g","proteinContent":"14 g","fatContent":"14 g","saturatedFatContent":"2 g","sodiumContent":"554 mg","fiberContent":"1 g","sugarContent":"13 g","unsaturatedFatContent":"11 g"},"@id":"https://thefoodietakesflight.com/shredded-tofu-bulgogi/#recipe","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://thefoodietakesflight.com/shredded-tofu-bulgogi/"},"mainEntityOfPage":"https://thefoodietakesflight.com/shredded-tofu-bulgogi/"}]}</script>
