<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="ftf-steps">STEPS</h2>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="ftf-for-the-shredded-tofu">FOR THE SHREDDED TOFU</h2>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>Remove the tofu from the water and drain from any excess water. Using a cheese grater, carefully grate the tofu into shreds.</li>



<li>Meanwhile, preheat your air-fryer or oven to 350F/180C.</li>



<li>On a lined baking tray or air fryer basket (I used parchment paper), place the shredded tofu and try to spread it out as thin as possible.</li>
</ul>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>For air-frying, air-fry for 12-15 minutes or until lightly golden brown - do not overcook since it can easily harden and become too dry.</li>



<li>You can flip the tofu halfway through cooking. It’s also okay not to get even browning and even have the tofu still white, since this can add to the different textures of the overall tofu dish.</li>
</ul>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>If baking, you may need to bake the tofu for 25-30 minutes.</li>
</ul>



