<div class="wprm-recipe-summary wprm-block-text-normal">Shredding tofu and baking or air-frying it to draw out excess creates a unique texture that almost resembles ground meat. This shredded tofu is cooked down in a bulgogi-style sauce that’s spicy, savoury, a little sweet, and oh-so flavourful. It’s a delicious tofu recipe you can prepare to serve over rice.</div>
